Sure, I can help you build a one-page website about homebrew beer using HTML and CSS. Here's an example code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Homebrew Beer</title>
    <style>
      /* CSS styles */
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }
      header {
        background-color: #333;
        color: #fff;
        padding: 20px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      h1 {
        margin: 0;
      }
      main {
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .section-heading {
        font-size: 24px;
        margin-top: 40px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .section-text {
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.5;
        margin-top: 20px;
        text-align: justify;
      }
      .section-image {
        display: block;
        margin: 0 auto;
        max-width: 100%;
      }
      footer {
        background-color: #333;
        color: #fff;
        padding: 20px;
        text-align: center;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- Header section -->
    <header>
      <h1>Homebrew Beer</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Main section -->
    <main>
      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">What is Homebrew Beer?</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          Homebrew beer is beer that is made at home, using equipment and
          ingredients that are easily available. It is a popular hobby among
          beer enthusiasts, as it allows them to create unique and customized
          brews that are not available in stores.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">How to Brew Your Own Beer</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          Brewing your own beer is a fun and rewarding process. To get started,
          you will need to purchase a homebrewing kit, which includes all the
          necessary equipment and ingredients. The process involves mixing
          water, malted barley, hops, and yeast in a large pot, then fermenting
          the mixture in a carboy for several weeks. Once the beer has
          fermented, it can be bottled or kegged for drinking.
        </p>
        <img
          src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1578357456354-71d659b7a12a"
          alt="Homebrew beer equipment"
          class="section-image"
        />
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Types of Homebrew Beer</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
          There are many different types of homebrew beer that you can make,
          including pale ales, stouts, IPAs, and lagers. Each type of beer has
          its own unique flavor and characteristics, which can be customized
          by adjusting the ingredients and brewing process.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <!-- Footer section -->
    <footer>
      <p>&copy; 2023 Homebrew Beer. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
```

