HTML:
```
<header>
  <nav>
    <div class="menu-btn">
      <div class="menu-btn__burger"></div>
    </div>
    <ul class="menu">
      <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</header>
```

CSS:
```
header {
  background-color: #fff;
  height: 70px;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 0 20px;
}

.menu {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  list-style: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  background-color: #fff;
  position: absolute;
  top: 70px;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  z-index: 1;
  height: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: height 0.3s ease-in-out;
}

.menu li {
  margin: 0;
}

.menu li a {
  display: block;
  padding: 10px;
  color: #333;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 1.2em;
}

.menu li a:hover {
  background-color: #f7f7f7;
}

.menu-btn {
  display: block;
  position: relative;
  width: 30px;
  height: 20px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.menu-btn__burger {
  position: absolute;
  width: 100%;
  height: 3px;
  background-color: #333;
  border-radius: 3px;
  left: 0;
  top: 50%;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
  transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out;
}

.menu-btn__burger::before,
.menu-btn__burger::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  width: 100%;
  height: 3px;
  background-color: #333;
  border-radius: 3px;
  transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out;
}

.menu-btn__burger::before {
  transform: translateY(-8px);
}

.menu-btn__burger::after {
  transform: translateY(8px);
}

.menu-btn.open .menu-btn__burger {
  background-color: transparent;
}

.menu-btn.open .menu-btn__burger::before {
  transform: translateY(0) rotate(45deg);
}

.menu-btn.open .menu-btn__burger::after {
  transform: translateY(0) rotate(-45deg);
}

.menu-btn.open ~ .menu {
  height: 150px;
}
```

This creates a basic header with a hamburger menu. The menu is initially hidden with a height of 0, and is revealed when the `.menu-btn` is clicked and given the `.open` class. The hamburger menu is created using a `div` with the class `.menu-btn__burger` and two pseudo-elements `::before` and `::after` for the top and bottom lines. The animation is created using CSS transitions and the `.open` class is added and removed using JavaScript or jQuery.

