JavaScript:
```
const menuIcon = document.querySelector('.menu-icon');
const menu = document.querySelector('.menu');

menuIcon.addEventListener('click', () => {
  menu.classList.toggle('show');
});
```

In this example, the menu icon consists of three horizontal lines (`.menu-icon__line`). When the user clicks on the icon (`.menu-icon`), the `.menu` element is toggled between the hidden and visible states by adding or removing the `.show` class.

